CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 19, 1958, pg. B6, reads: "M. Lifsher's Work - M. Lifsher and Son, 809 E. Carson St., home improvement experts for over 28 years, recently remodeled Mrs. Syvella Williams' home on Iowa St. Mrs. Williams designed these changes and they were very ably carried out by M. Lifsher and Son... Bottom left: A view of the hallway showing a portion of the new lowered door.  New vinlyn tile is on the floor...  Harris Photo. - Adv."
TitMainTitle: Hallway with checkered floor remodeled by M. Lifsher and Son in home of Syvella Williams, Iowa Street
